javadoc:
The ToolStateHistoryService maintains a stack of locations that the user 
 has visited via a navigation plugin.  
 It provides methods querying and manipulating this list.

methods.javadoc:
Positions the "current" location to the next location in the history list.
 If there is no "next" location, the history list remains unchanged.
methods.name: next
methods.comment:
Positions the "current" location to the next location in the history list.
 If there is no "next" location, the history list remains unchanged.

methods.javadoc:
Positions the "current" location to the previous location in the history list.
 If there is no "previous" location, the
 history list remains unchanged.
methods.name: previous
methods.comment:
Positions the "current" location to the previous location in the history list.
 If there is no "previous" location, the
 history list remains unchanged.

methods.name: next
methods.comment:
Navigates to the given location in the "next" list.  If the location is not in the list, then
 nothing will happen.

params.name: location
params.comment: The location within the "next" list to which to go.

methods.name: previous
methods.comment:
Navigates to the given location in the "previous" list.  If the location is not in 
 the list, then nothing will happen.

params.name: location
params.comment: The location within the "previous" list to which to go.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the LocationMemento objects in the "previous" list.
@return the LocationMemento objects in the "previous" list.
methods.name: getPreviousLocations
methods.comment: Returns the LocationMemento objects in the "previous" list.

return.comment: the LocationMemento objects in the "previous" list.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the LocationMemento objects in the "next" list.
@return the LocationMemento objects in the "next" list.
methods.name: getNextLocations
methods.comment: Returns the LocationMemento objects in the "next" list.

return.comment: the LocationMemento objects in the "next" list.

methods.javadoc: Returns true if there is a valid "next" location in the history list.
methods.name: hasNext
methods.comment: Returns true if there is a valid "next" location in the history list.

methods.javadoc: Returns true if there is a valid "previous" location in the history list.
methods.name: hasPrevious
methods.comment: Returns true if there is a valid "previous" location in the history list.

methods.javadoc:
Adds the given locationMomento to the list of previous locations.  Clears the list
 of next locations.

methods.comment:
Adds the given locationMomento to the list of previous locations.  Clears the list
 of next locations.

methods.javadoc: Removes all visited locations from the history list.
methods.name: clear
methods.comment: Removes all visited locations from the history list.
